Schedule-Pluggable version 0.0.1

NAME    Schedule::Pluggable

  Schedule::Pluggable is a perl module which provides the ability to run
  processes in a simple and highly controllable way using plugins.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

Alternatively, to install with Module::Build, you can use the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install


DEPENDENCIES

Moose
MooseX::Workers
MooseX::Object::Pluggable


